<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="1860" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,1424,1588]" box="[160,285,1424,1449]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,285,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">Etymology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,1424,1588]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">
Combination of Melayu and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="d' Audebard de Ferussac" authorityYear="1821" box="[488,562,1460,1484]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Onchis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[488,562,1460,1484]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">Onchis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Melayu is the Malay word for Malays. It is selected here because the core of the known distribution of the new genus described here mostly corresponds to the historical Malay world – that is, Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[940,1036,1529,1553]" name="Malaysia" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(including 
<collectingCountry box="[160,276,1564,1588]" name="Singapore" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">Singapore</collectingCountry>
) and coastal Borneo. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="d' Audebard de Ferussac" authorityYear="1821" box="[523,597,1564,1588]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Onchis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[523,597,1564,1588]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">Onchis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the names used for onchidiid slugs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="1861" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,1633,1727]" box="[160,276,1633,1658]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,1633,1658]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[160,1155,1633,1727]" lastBlockId="11.[160,1156,142,236]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="1861" pageId="10" pageNumber="1860">
Body not flattened. No marginal glands in the notum. No dorsal gills. Dorsal eyes present on notum. Fully retractable, central papilla (with three dorsal eyes) present. Short eye tentacles. Male opening below the right ocular tentacle, slightly to its left. Pneumostome median. Intestine of 
<typeStatus box="[385,445,177,201]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">types</typeStatus>
II and III (and intermediary between 
<typeStatus box="[849,909,177,201]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">types</typeStatus>
II and III). Rectal gland present. Accessory penial gland and hollow spine present or absent. Penis with no hooks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1156,288,1145]" box="[160,262,288,313]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,288,313]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1156,288,1145]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">
A new generic name is needed because no existing name could apply to the clade described here. We provide here a few remarks on the status of the generic names that are potentially valid in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Dayrat 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Dayrat" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[450,760,393,417]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
Onchidiidae (
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B" box="[606,752,393,417]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref21005" refString="Dayrat B. 2009. Review of the current knowledge of the systematics of Onchidiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Pulmonata) with a checklist of nominal species. Zootaxa. 2068: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">Dayrat 2009</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Our remarks are based on the examination of all the 
<typeStatus box="[417,467,427,451]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">type</typeStatus>
specimens available, especially those of all the 
<typeStatus box="[1010,1060,427,451]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">type</typeStatus>
species, as well as the careful analysis of all the original descriptions (especially when no 
<typeStatus box="[1105,1155,462,486]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">type</typeStatus>
specimens were available). More details will be provided in our revisions of the corresponding genera. However, here we do not comment on the generic names that refer to 
<taxonomicName authority="J. E. Gray, 1850" authorityName="J. E. Gray" authorityYear="1850" box="[160,450,566,590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Onchidella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,276,566,590]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Onchidella</emphasis>
J.E. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gray JE" box="[329,450,566,590]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" refId="ref21441" refString="Gray JE. 1850. Figures of molluscous animals selected from various authors. Etched for the use of students by M. E. Gray. Vol. 4. London: Longman, Brown, Green and Longmans; p. iv + 219 p." type="book" year="1850">Gray, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Strand, 1932" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1932" box="[511,807,566,590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Hoffmannola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,654,566,590]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Hoffmannola</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Strand E" box="[663,807,566,590]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="193 - 196" refId="ref22061" refString="Strand E. 1932. Miscellanea nomenclatorica zoologica et palaeontologica. Fol Zool Hydrobiol. 4: 193 - 196." type="journal article" year="1932">Strand, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which are not represented in the tropical Indo-West Pacific (
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B" box="[501,638,601,625]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="1 - 26" refId="ref21005" refString="Dayrat B. 2009. Review of the current knowledge of the systematics of Onchidiidae (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Pulmonata) with a checklist of nominal species. Zootaxa. 2068: 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2009">Dayrat 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B &amp; Zimmermann S &amp; Raposa M" box="[650,861,601,625]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="939 - 1003" refId="ref21237" refString="Dayrat B, Zimmermann S, Raposa M. 2011 b. Systematic revision of the Onchidiidae from the Tropical Eastern Pacific. J Nat Hist. 45: 939 - 1003." type="journal article" year="2011">Dayrat et al. 2011b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Avila-Poveda OH &amp; Abadia-Chanona QY &amp; Herrera-Fragoso R &amp; Dayrat B" box="[874,1142,601,625]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="463 - 471" refId="ref20819" refString="Avila-Poveda OH, Abadia-Chanona QY, Herrera-Fragoso R, Dayrat B. 2014. Review of the geographic distribution of Hoffmannola hansi (Gastropoda: Pulmonata) in the Mexican Pacific. Rev Mex Biodiv. 85: 463 - 471." type="journal article" year="2014">Avila-Poveda et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Several generic names apply to a clade including all the onchidiid slugs with dorsal gills – that is, 
<taxonomicName authority="Fleming, 1822" authorityName="Fleming" authorityYear="1822" box="[242,486,670,694]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Peronia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[242,321,670,694]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Peronia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fleming J" box="[330,486,670,694]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" refId="ref21303" refString="Fleming J. 1822 - 1824. Peronia. In: Encyclopedia Britannica, vol. 5. Supplement to the 4 - 6 th edition. Edinburgh. p. 574." type="book" year="1822">Fleming, 1822</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Gistel, 1848" authorityName="Gistel" authorityYear="1848" box="[498,733,670,694]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Eudrastus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,599,670,694]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Eudrastus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gistel J" box="[607,733,670,694]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" refId="ref21420" refString="Gistel J. 1848. Naturgeschichte des Thierreichs fur hohere Schulen. Stuttgart: Hoffmann; p. 216 p." type="book" year="1848">Gistel, 1848</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Starobogatov, 1976" authorityName="Starobogatov" authorityYear="1976" box="[747,1070,670,694]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Lessonina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,849,670,694]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Lessonina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Starobogatov YI" box="[858,1070,670,694]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="206 - 212" refId="ref22009" refString="Starobogatov YI. 1976. Composition and taxonomic position of marine pulmonate mollusks. Sov J Mar Biol. 4: 206 - 212." type="journal article" year="1976">Starobogatov, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="d' Audebard de Ferussac, 1821" authorityName="d' Audebard de Ferussac" authorityYear="1821" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Onchis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1084,1155,670,694]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Onchis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="d' Audebard de Ferussac JBL" box="[160,490,704,729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" refId="ref20917" refString="d' Audebard de Ferussac JBL. 1821. Tableaux systematiques des animaux mollusques classes en familles naturelles, dans lesquels on a etabli la concordance de tous les systemes. Paris: A. Bertrand; p. XLVIII + 110 p." type="book" year="1821">d’ Audebard de Férussac, 1821</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Labbe, 1934" authorityName="Labbe" authorityYear="1934" box="[504,773,705,729]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Paraperonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[504,631,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Paraperonia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Labbe A" box="[640,773,705,729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="173 - 246" refId="ref21566" refString="Labbe A. 1934. Les Silicodermes (Labbe) du Museum d' Histoire Naturelle de Paris. Premiere partie: classification, nouvelles ou peu connues. Ann Inst Ocean Monaco. 14: 173 - 246." type="journal article" year="1934">Labbé, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Starobogatov, 1976" authorityName="Starobogatov" authorityYear="1976" box="[787,1100,705,729]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Quoyella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,879,705,729]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Quoyella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Starobogatov YI" box="[887,1100,705,729]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="206 - 212" refId="ref22009" refString="Starobogatov YI. 1976. Composition and taxonomic position of marine pulmonate mollusks. Sov J Mar Biol. 4: 206 - 212." type="journal article" year="1976">Starobogatov, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and 
<taxonomicName authority="Labbe, 1934" authorityName="Labbe" authorityYear="1934" box="[160,381,739,763]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Scaphis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,239,739,763]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Scaphis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Labbe A" box="[247,381,739,763]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="173 - 246" refId="ref21566" refString="Labbe A. 1934. Les Silicodermes (Labbe) du Museum d' Histoire Naturelle de Paris. Premiere partie: classification, nouvelles ou peu connues. Ann Inst Ocean Monaco. 14: 173 - 246." type="journal article" year="1934">Labbé, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The generic name 
<emphasis box="[603,678,739,763]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Labella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Starobogatov YI" box="[686,899,739,763]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="206 - 212" refId="ref22009" refString="Starobogatov YI. 1976. Composition and taxonomic position of marine pulmonate mollusks. Sov J Mar Biol. 4: 206 - 212." type="journal article" year="1976">Starobogatov, 1976</bibRefCitation>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Buchannan, 1800" authorityName="Buchannan" authorityYear="1800" box="[160,473,774,798]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Onchidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,275,774,798]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Onchidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Buchannan F" box="[284,473,774,798]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="132 - 134" refId="ref20878" refString="Buchannan F. 1800. An account of the Onchidium, a new genus of the class of vermes, found in Bengal. Trans Lin Soc London. 5: 132 - 134, pl. 5." type="journal article" year="1800">Buchannan, 1800</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which applies to a different clade including the 
<typeStatus box="[1020,1068,774,798]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Buchannan, 1800" authorityName="Buchannan" authorityYear="1800" box="[160,556,809,833]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Onchidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="typhae">
<emphasis box="[160,357,809,833]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Onchidium typhae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Buchannan F" box="[366,556,809,833]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="132 - 134" refId="ref20878" refString="Buchannan F. 1800. An account of the Onchidium, a new genus of the class of vermes, found in Bengal. Trans Lin Soc London. 5: 132 - 134, pl. 5." type="journal article" year="1800">Buchannan, 1800</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and is characterised by large conical papillae on the dorsal notum (
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B &amp; Goulding TC &amp; Apte D &amp; Bhave V &amp; Comendador J &amp; Ngo XQ &amp; Tan SK &amp; Tan SH" box="[322,519,843,867]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref21184" refString="Dayrat B, Goulding TC, Apte D, Bhave V, Comendador J, Ngo XQ, Tan SK, Tan SH. 2016. Integrative taxonomy of the genus Onchidium Buchannan, 1800 (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Onchidiidae). ZooKeys. 636: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2016">Dayrat et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The generic name 
<taxonomicName authority="Labbe, 1934" authorityName="Labbe" authorityYear="1934" box="[749,1036,843,867]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Paraoncidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[749,894,843,867]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Paraoncidium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Labbe A" box="[903,1036,843,867]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="173 - 246" refId="ref21566" refString="Labbe A. 1934. Les Silicodermes (Labbe) du Museum d' Histoire Naturelle de Paris. Premiere partie: classification, nouvelles ou peu connues. Ann Inst Ocean Monaco. 14: 173 - 246." type="journal article" year="1934">Labbé, 1934</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Semper, 1885" authorityName="Semper" authorityYear="1885" box="[295,559,878,902]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Onchidina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[295,403,878,902]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Onchidina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Semper C" box="[410,559,878,902]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="251 - 290" refId="ref21956" refString="Semper C. 1885. Dritte familie, onchidiidae. In: Semper C, editor. Reisen im Archipel der Philippinen, Wissenschaftliche Resultate, III (7). Wiesbaden: C. W. Kreidel; p. p. 251 - 290, pls. XIX - XXVII." type="book chapter" year="1885">Semper, 1885</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
which applies to a species with no dorsal eyes (Dayrat and Goulding submitted). 
<taxonomicName authority="von Plate, 1893" authorityName="von Plate" authorityYear="1893" box="[437,696,913,937]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Peronina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[437,530,913,937]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Peronina</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Von Plate L" box="[534,696,913,937]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="93 - 234" refId="ref22243" refString="Von Plate L. 1893. Studien uber opisthopneumone Lungeschnecken, II, Die Oncidiidien. Zool Jahrb Anat Ontog Thiere. 7: 93 - 234, pls. 7 - 12." type="journal article" year="1893">von Plate, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
applies to its 
<typeStatus box="[837,885,913,937]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="von Plate, 1893" authorityName="von Plate" authorityYear="1893" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Peronina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alta">
<emphasis box="[972,1110,913,937]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Peronina alta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Von Plate L" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="93 - 234" refId="ref22243" refString="Von Plate L. 1893. Studien uber opisthopneumone Lungeschnecken, II, Die Oncidiidien. Zool Jahrb Anat Ontog Thiere. 7: 93 - 234, pls. 7 - 12." type="journal article" year="1893">von Plate, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, characterised by a pneumostome distinctly and unusually located on the margin of the notum (a feature that is present in the 
<typeStatus box="[637,685,982,1006]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="von Plate" authorityYear="1893" box="[810,948,982,1006]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Peronina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alta">
<emphasis box="[810,948,982,1006]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Peronina alta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Baker, 1938" authorityName="Baker" authorityYear="1938" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Platevindex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[966,1085,982,1006]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Platevindex</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Baker HB" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref20861" refString="Baker HB. 1938. Nomenclature of Onchidiidae. Nautilus. 51: 85 - 88." type="journal article" year="1938">Baker, 1938</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
applies to a clade including species with a distinctly flattened body and narrow foot, such as the 
<typeStatus box="[233,281,1051,1075]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Semper 1885)" baseAuthorityName="Semper" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[374,773,1051,1075]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Platevindex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="coriaceum">
<emphasis box="[374,608,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Platevindex coriaceum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Semper C" box="[621,766,1051,1075]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="251 - 290" refId="ref21956" refString="Semper C. 1885. Dritte familie, onchidiidae. In: Semper C, editor. Reisen im Archipel der Philippinen, Wissenschaftliche Resultate, III (7). Wiesbaden: C. W. Kreidel; p. p. 251 - 290, pls. XIX - XXVII." type="book chapter" year="1885">Semper 1885</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Finally, 
<taxonomicName authority="Starobogatov, 1976" authorityName="Starobogatov" authorityYear="1976" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Semperoncis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[866,997,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Semperoncis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Starobogatov YI" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="206 - 212" refId="ref22009" refString="Starobogatov YI. 1976. Composition and taxonomic position of marine pulmonate mollusks. Sov J Mar Biol. 4: 206 - 212." type="journal article" year="1976">Starobogatov, 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
applies to species that are adapted to terrestrial life in the 
<collectingCountry box="[839,957,1086,1110]" name="Philippines" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Philippines</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B" box="[968,1110,1086,1110]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref21042" refString="Dayrat B. 2010 a. Anatomical re-description of the terrestrial onchidiid slug Semperoncis montana (Plate, 1893). Malacologia. 52: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="2010">Dayrat 2010a</bibRefCitation>
). As no other generic name exists for the taxon described here, a new name is needed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1156,1197,1430]" box="[160,521,1197,1222]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,521,1197,1222]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Distinctive diagnostic features</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[160,1156,1197,1430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">
No external diagnostic feature seems to unambiguously distinguish 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dayrat and Goulding" authorityYear="2017" box="[927,1061,1233,1257]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Melayonchis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,1061,1233,1257]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Melayonchis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all other genera (which is not surprising because many onchidiid species from different genera look very similar externally). Internally, however, the lateral radular teeth of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dayrat and Goulding" authorityYear="2017" box="[160,294,1337,1361]" class="Gastropoda" family="Onchidiidae" genus="Melayonchis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Systellommatophora" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,294,1337,1361]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Melayonchis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterised by a protuberance on their inner lateral margin (see arrows in 
<figureCitation box="[275,381,1371,1395]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="18.[160,225,1149,1172]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1114]" captionTargetId="figure-137@18.[163,1152,142,1118]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 6. Radula, Melayonchis eloisae. (a) Innermost lateral and lateral teeth, Malaysia (USMMC 00007, 1). (b) Lateral teeth, Brunei Darussalam (BDMNH, 1). (c) Rachidian tooth, Malaysia (USMMC 00007, 1). (d) Outermost lateral teeth, Malaysia (USMMC 00007, 1). (e) Lateral teeth, detail, Brunei Darussalam (BDMNH, 1). The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a = 40 mm; b = 30 μm; c = 10 μm; d = 20 μm; e = 5 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182662" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182662/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">Figures 6</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[394,424,1371,1395]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="27.[160,225,1141,1164]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-146@27.[163,1152,142,1110]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 13. Radula, Melayonchis siongkiati. (a) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth, Malaysia (USMMC 00016,2). (b) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth, same as (a). (c) Outermost lateral teeth,same as (a). (d) Lateral teeth, same as (a). (e) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth, Brunei Darussalam, station 30 (BDMNH, 1). (f) Lateral teeth, inferior view, same as (e). The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a, d = 40 μm; b, c, e = 20 μm; f = 4 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182676/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[436,466,1371,1395]" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="33.[160,225,1137,1160]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1105]" captionTargetId="figure-31@33.[163,1152,142,1106]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="Figure 18. Radula, Melayonchis annae, Singapore (ZRC.MOL.6503, 2). (a) Median region of left half rows. (b) Rachidian and innermost lateral teeth. (c) Lateral teeth, inferior view. (d) Outermost lateral teeth. (e) Lateral teeth. The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a = 100 μm; b, d, e = 20 μm; c = 4 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182686/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">18</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[478,505,1371,1395]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="40.[160,225,1139,1162]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,1108]" captionTargetId="figure-159@40.[163,1152,142,1108]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figure 24. Radula, Melayonchis aileenae, Malaysia (USMMC 00019, 2). (a) Median region of left half rows. (b) Rachidian and innermost teeth. (c) Rachidian and innermost teeth. (d) Outermost lateral teeth. (e) Lateral teeth. The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Scale bars: a = 40 μm; b, e = 10 μm; c, d = 5 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182698" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182698/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">24</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[567,596,1371,1395]" captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="41.[160,225,824,847]" captionTargetBox="[163,1152,142,783]" captionTargetId="figure-58@41.[163,1152,142,793]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="Figure 25. Radula, Melayonchis aileenae, Malaysia. (a) Innermost lateral and lateral teeth (USMMC 00019, 1). (b) Rachidian tooth (USMMC 00019, 1). (c) Lateral teeth, inferior view (USMMC 00019, 1). (d) Outermost lateral teeth (USMMC 00021). The arrows indicate the lateral protuberance which is characteristic of the teeth in Melayonchis. Sclae bars: a, d = 20 μm; b, c = 5 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5182700" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5182700/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861">25</figureCitation>
) which is a distinctive feature that has not been observed in any other species so far (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B" box="[622,770,1406,1430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref21042" refString="Dayrat B. 2010 a. Anatomical re-description of the terrestrial onchidiid slug Semperoncis montana (Plate, 1893). Malacologia. 52: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="2010">Dayrat 2010a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B" box="[782,854,1406,1430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="87 - 101" refId="ref21071" refString="Dayrat B. 2010 b. Comparative anatomy and taxonomy of Onchidium vaigiense Quoy and Gaimard, 1824. Moll Res. 30: 87 - 101." type="journal article" year="2010">2010b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B &amp; Zimmermann S &amp; Raposa M" box="[864,1075,1406,1430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="939 - 1003" refId="ref21237" refString="Dayrat B, Zimmermann S, Raposa M. 2011 b. Systematic revision of the Onchidiidae from the Tropical Eastern Pacific. J Nat Hist. 45: 939 - 1003." type="journal article" year="2011">
Dayrat et al. 2011 
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat B &amp; Goulding TC &amp; Apte D &amp; Bhave V &amp; Comendador J &amp; Ngo XQ &amp; Tan SK &amp; Tan SH" box="[1062,1075,1406,1430]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1861" pagination="1 - 40" refId="ref21184" refString="Dayrat B, Goulding TC, Apte D, Bhave V, Comendador J, Ngo XQ, Tan SK, Tan SH. 2016. Integrative taxonomy of the genus Onchidium Buchannan, 1800 (Mollusca, Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Onchidiidae). ZooKeys. 636: 1 - 40." type="journal article" year="2016">b</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 2016).
</paragraph>
